# agent-toolbelt Router

Use installed agent-toolbelt workflows when the task clearly matches one. Prefer
the matching slash command or skill over re-creating the workflow from memory.

Use `/workflow-router` when the right workflow is unclear.

Common matches:

- Feature or app work needing brief, flows, acceptance criteria, phased
  implementation, commits, and reviews: `dev-lite-workflow`.
- Traceable feature delivery with formal docs, gates, QA, and release artifacts:
  `ai-feature-delivery`.
- Code review: `pr-review`.
- Debugging from symptom to fix: `bug-to-fix`.
- Review comment follow-up: `pr-review-reply`.
- Phase gate or merge readiness: `phase-gate`.

General guardrails:

- Respect existing repo instructions and project conventions.
- Keep edits scoped to the user's task.
- Avoid destructive git or filesystem actions unless explicitly requested.
- Run relevant checks when practical; otherwise say what was not run and why.
- Put workflow-specific procedures, rubrics, and checklists in the matching skill
  context instead of applying them to unrelated chats.
